# OPS/_llm/80 — extract the question + retrieve (keyword mode).
#
# op://select is a BUNDLED compute (the colocated select.js builds to
# wasm at `txco apply` time). It does the two things txcl cannot:
# address the LAST user message (no negative indexing in path grammar)
# and flatten string-vs-block-array content. It writes the question to
# `_question` for the vector path, and in keyword mode scores the
# decision log and emits up to two `@llm.context` items — the GATEWAY
# then owns budget, dedup, the guard block, and serialization into
# system content. The nano-op returns ONLY its delta: returning the
# whole envelope would array-append request.messages on merge.
WHEN @src == "llm" && @llm.phase == "request"
  EXEC "op://select"
